<div id="Idea_3565"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3565-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3565">Central Repositories&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/6746-4049">farseer2002</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">4 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The federal government should create and maintain a set of central libraries of ALL federal documents released to the public.  The Department of Energy through OSTI has made a good beginning at doing this with the Energy Citations Database.  <br/><br/>That database, good as it is, is incomplete and most newer documents take a long time to be posted.  ALL new documents should be posted immediately.</div>
